<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-09T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="897" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/125: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-09T11:00:00+02:00">April 9, 1929—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 9—8:55 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>24. My 2, April 4, 5 p.m., from Angora. Exchange of notes putting into
                            effect commercial <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> between the
                            United States and Turkey for one year from April 11th, 1929, took place
                            yesterday afternoon. Customs authorities throughout Turkey
                            telegraphically notified from Angora.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>